import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by=['year'])
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['wheat'], color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Wheat Production')
    plt.title('What is the trend of wheat production over the years?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['wages'], bins=10, color='green', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['wages'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['wages'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.xlabel('Wages')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wages in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y')
    data = data.set_index('year')
    data = data.resample('Y').mean()
    ax = data.plot(kind='bar', figsize=(12, 6), legend=False)
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Average Wheat Production')
    ax.axhline(y=data['wheat'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Average')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average wheat production per year?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

chart = plot(data)
